result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
10:01 am - 15CM13 & 15CM14 - Defendant Molly Ann Nessman appeared with attorney Corey Mehlos.  Mark T. Fuhr appeared for the State of Wisconsin. DA states agreement. DA certifies victims rights compliance. DA moves to amend 15CM13 to Price Co. Ord. 90-1.  So ordered. DE pleads NO CONTEST to 15CM13.  Court accepts plea, finds DE guilty and orders JOC on 15CM13 and on motion of DA dismisses and reads in 15CM14 for purposes of paying service fees. Adj. 10:05 am. 

Court imposes (15CM13): $295 fine; $130 SBDA ($65 for 15CM13 & $65 for 15CM14)
Payplan of $25/mo on or before 09-30-15 and $50/mo starting 11-30-15 until paid in full or CO.

If not already completed DE must submit to booking at Sheriff's Dept prior to release.  Defendant shall give written notice prior to any change in address or telephone number to the Clerk of this Court and Defense Attorney.  DE may not have contact with Debra Gulczynski, unless there is written consent on file.

10:13 am - 15CM13 & 15CM14 - Defendant Molly Ann Nessman appeared in court. Mark T. Fuhr appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Complaints acknowledged, reading waived.    DE plans to retain an attorney.  Court gives DE another notice of right to atty.  DE enters plea of NOT GUILTY to all counts.  Court orders Pre-trial conference be scheduled.  One bond for both cases.
